# sha256 of every shipped hooks.json that the installer is allowed to
# overwrite automatically. One hex digest per line; blank lines and
# `# comment` lines are ignored.
#
# Adding a new release that changes hooks.json:
#   1. Compute the *outgoing* (currently committed) file's hash and append
#      it here — this lets users on the prior release auto-upgrade.
#   2. Edit hooks.json.
#
# An installed ~/.codex/hooks.json whose hash is NOT in this list is treated
# as user-modified: the installer prompts on a TTY, skips with a warning
# otherwise.

